correctness.rationale: Several key elements are incorrect or untraceable and the extraction does not represent all distinct processes described. Major issues: (1) Missing processes: The article reports multiple IGZO variants (O2 plasma reference; N2O plasma 1 s and 5 s; selective N2O applied to In2O3, Ga2O3, or ZnO). Only one process instance is provided, violating the multi-process requirement. (2) Time units incorrect: Precursor and co-reactant dosing and purge times are reported in seconds in the article but encoded with unit MilliSEC without converting the numeric values (e.g., DADI 1.5 s should be 1500 ms; purges 25 s/10 s should be 25000/10000 ms). (3) Film thickness wrong: IGZO active layer used in devices is 10 nm; 20 nm is reported. (4) Co-reactant usage incomplete: Only O2 is listed; N2O plasma co-reactant and its selective application per cation (including 1 s and 5 s variants) are not captured. (5) Unsupported/fabricated parameters: Growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), total number of cycles (set to 18, which actually refers to In subcycles per supercycle, not total cycles), all flow rates (sccm values), uniformity, conformality, refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap for IGZO, resistivity, carrier density, roughness value, and film density are not provided in the article. (6) Composition fields inconsistent: Elemental concentration is given as a single 71.2% without specifying element; atomic ratio '1.0:2.8:5.4' does not match XRF data (Table S3 shows In 71.2%, Ga 7.8%, Zn 21.0; normalized ratio should reflect these values). (7) Some fields are correct: temperature (200 °C), pressure (1.2 Torr), plasma power (100 W), precursors (DADI/TMGa/DEZ), reactor description, supercycle sequence [In2O3×18–Ga2O3×1–ZnO×1], device structure (TGBC), and device metrics for the O2 reference (VTH, μFE, SS) match the article. Properties to correct/review: add separate processes for each reactant condition; fix dosing/purge times to ms; set film thickness to 10 nm; represent N2O co-reactant where applicable; remove or justify unsupported flow/GPC/film property values; correct elemental concentrations and atomic ratios to match XRF.

completeness.rationale: Incomplete and partially non-traceable. (1) Multiple processes are described in the article but only one process instance is extracted. Missing distinct processes include: reference O2-plasma IGZO; full N2O-plasma IGZO at 1 s and 5 s; and three selective N2O cases (In2O3-only, Ga2O3-only, ZnO-only) each at 1 s and 5 s (total ≈9 processes). (2) Reactant selection is incomplete: N2O co-reactant and its exposure times (1 s and 5 s) are not represented where applicable; coReactant is set to O2 for all compounds. (3) Dosing/purge time units violate schema and article: the article reports seconds, while the schema expects MilliSEC; values such as 1.5 s, 25 s, 10 s are encoded as 1.5, 25, 10 MilliSEC instead of 1500, 25000, 10000 ms. Plasma exposure time for O2 (1 s) and N2O (1/5 s) is not correctly captured. (4) Film thickness is incorrect: IGZO active layer is 10 nm, not 20 nm (20 nm corresponds to Al2O3 gate insulator). (5) numberofCycles is misused: 18 is the In2O3 subcycles per supercycle, not the total ALD cycles (which are not reported). (6) Several properties are fabricated or not traceable to the article: growth-per-cycle values, flow rates (sccm), uniformity, conformality, refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap of IGZO, resistivity/carrier density of IGZO, film density, on/off ratio. (7) Composition fields are inconsistent: atomicRatio does not match XRF (should reflect ~In 71.2%, Ga 7.8%, Zn 21.0); elementalConcentration lists only a single value without element mapping. (8) DeliveryMethod is misused (it describes the plasma source rather than delivery method). To improve completeness: add separate process objects for each IGZO condition (O2, full N2O 1 s/5 s, and selective N2O for each cation at 1 s/5 s); set co-reactants and plasma times accordingly; correct time units to ms; correct IGZO film thickness to 10 nm; remove or justify unsupported properties; align composition with XRF; and review numberofCycles to reflect total cycles or justify if unavailable.
